1
00:00:00,590 --> 00:00:03,880
Hi all subscribers and viewers of my channel.

2
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:13,200
Today we'll examine several interesting moments people face in the tuning process.

3
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,400
The question.

4
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:24,200
The first of this format: I tuned a Tesla transformer to quarter wave by your calculations.

5
00:00:24,940 --> 00:00:27,780
Now I want to retune it to half wave.

6
00:00:27,780 --> 00:00:34,600
But when I calculate frequencies, my math doesn't add up.

7
00:00:34,860 --> 00:00:43,700
And if by math I switch to the frequency I calculated, the coil doesn't settle in any way.

8
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:45,040
And what to do with this?

9
00:00:45,620 --> 00:00:47,400
And are the calculations correct at all?

10
00:00:48,400 --> 00:01:01,560
On this schematic picture I drew here conventionally the standing wave distribution in the Tesla transformer.

11
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:06,460
The same concerns the system on the grenade with grounding.

12
00:01:06,820 --> 00:01:17,420
How currents and voltage are distributed in the case when the system stands at quarter wave, and in the case when the system stands at half wave.

13
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:33,720
It turns out that to fix the moment when our system is in quarter, we should get maximum voltage at the upper hot end of the Tesla transformer, at its isolated capacity.

14
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:40,540
At that, the maximum current will be at the lower end of the Tesla transformer.

15
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:46,000
This part — this is the grounding wire and its wave distributions.

16
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:55,920
The thing is, usually only this part is considered, and they forget what's happening at this moment in the grounding.

17
00:01:56,160 --> 00:02:02,070
And in the grounding the picture happens in antiphase to what happens in the resonator.

18
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:17,590
So if the system as a whole became at quarter wave, effectively the whole system forms an integral picture, and we get this half-wave distribution.

19
00:02:18,010 --> 00:02:23,530
But only a quarter of the standing wave is in our Tesla transformer.

20
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:31,470
Another situation, more interesting, we get when the system becomes at half wave.

21
00:02:32,070 --> 00:02:42,570
In this case the point of voltage maximum moves from the hot end of the Tesla transformer to the middle of the coil.

22
00:02:42,570 --> 00:02:56,470
At that, the current distributes differently, since between them there's a 90-degree shift, and the frequency here is higher, so this point moved with the rising of frequency.

23
00:02:57,030 --> 00:03:03,550
The wavelength shortens, and it distributes differently along the length of our coil.

24
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:07,590
So the ratio turns out like this.

25
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:16,750
At half-wave distribution on our Tesla transformer, the current will be in antiphase at its ends.

26
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:23,930
At that, also don't forget as always about the grounding part that's here with us.

27
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:30,050
Here an integral figure also forms, and only now we get a full wave here.

28
00:03:31,050 --> 00:03:35,970
If you consider the system as a whole, only half a wave falls on our resonator.

29
00:03:37,590 --> 00:03:41,350
What calculations does a person do?

30
00:03:42,050 --> 00:03:49,770
For example, I'll show calculations for my real coil so it's understandable with its example.

31
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:53,630
The action logic is simple.

32
00:03:55,350 --> 00:04:12,290
A person calculates the Tesla transformer, then takes the quarter-wave resonance frequency, multiplies it by 2, and gets the frequency for the half wave on this resonator.

33
00:04:12,890 --> 00:04:22,130
The thing is, here already there's idealized math, and for those who believe in it — in all these formulas and so on — it doesn't work.

34
00:04:22,790 --> 00:04:41,010
If for quarter-wave resonance up to frequency 1.5 MHz you can still calculate wave speed through the known speed of light, then applying these calculations to a half-wave resonator already can't be done.

35
00:04:41,910 --> 00:04:44,090
There'll be very large errors.

36
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:50,010
And now in practice we'll examine what errors come out in reality.

37
00:04:50,710 --> 00:05:04,510
To move to the practical part, to start we need a simple device with which we'll track antinode and voltage in our coil.

38
00:05:05,390 --> 00:05:23,710
I made it from a piece of copper wire 65 cm long — the wire folds practically in half, the system length comes out to 30 cm from the neon bulb to the point where we'll hold with fingers.

39
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:34,990
A system from copper wire, to the end of which a neon bulb is soldered, and the connection looks like this.

40
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:42,170
One contact I solder to the copper, and the other contact bend into this form.

41
00:05:42,170 --> 00:05:49,310
Now we have a convenient probe for determining the voltage antinode on the Tesla transformer.

42
00:05:50,250 --> 00:06:16,770
We'll supply frequency to the Tesla transformer with the help of a lab signal generator, and through it, changing its frequency, we'll determine via this indicator: does math actually show us the truth, that multiplying the quarter-wave resonance frequency we determine half wave, and what problems are connected with this.

43
00:06:16,910 --> 00:06:28,450
Before you is our test specimen, my Tesla transformer, with conductor length 149 m, calculated frequency 500 kHz.

44
00:06:28,450 --> 00:06:40,290
I made this transformer on a frame from air ducts, white plastic, using wire of 0.96 mm cross-section.

45
00:06:40,770 --> 00:06:52,930
For it I also picked the isolated capacity, combined the wave distribution on wire length with LC resonance with the help of additional isolated capacity.

46
00:06:53,370 --> 00:07:10,190
The Tesla transformer in this case is now connected to grounding, and at the base of the Tesla transformer coil there's one turn of conductor, to which we'll supply the signal from the lab generator.

47
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:17,830
In the first case we examine the moment of tuning the Tesla transformer to quarter wave.

48
00:07:18,030 --> 00:07:24,630
Reminder, at quarter wave the voltage antinode will be at this point for us.

49
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:34,830
And accordingly the neon lamp should glow at this point, and as the neon lamp moves to the base of the transformer it'll go out.

50
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:40,110
I apply 500 kHz frequency.

51
00:07:42,310 --> 00:07:48,090
You see, the neon lamp glows, and as we lower it, it goes out.

52
00:07:48,090 --> 00:07:55,240
That is, the voltage antinode is clearly visible at the end of the winding of the high-voltage transformer.

53
00:07:55,730 --> 00:08:00,470
The neon lamp will also glow near the isolated capacity.

54
00:08:01,170 --> 00:08:08,300
With this moment, no special difficulty arises, and most often people do it successfully.

55
00:08:09,170 --> 00:08:18,250
If you do the calculations that I gave earlier on my channel, all these moments are present, and you can calculate by them.

56
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:22,510
We also fix the frequency in this experiment.

57
00:08:23,090 --> 00:08:27,030
Here it's visible on the lab signal generator at 500 kHz.

58
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:30,210
The neon lamp glows.

59
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:35,810
Now switch our system to half-wave mode.

60
00:08:35,810 --> 00:08:41,750
According to idealized math, we multiply our frequency by 2.

61
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:48,610
So I set the frequency here at 1 MHz.

62
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:58,030
Now at this frequency the neon lamp at the hot end of the Tesla transformer went out.

63
00:08:58,030 --> 00:09:08,730
And we can check whether the voltage antinode actually moved to the center of our coil.

64
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:17,740
Lead the indicator.

65
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:26,250
And as you see, the lamp doesn't glow anywhere.

66
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:30,550
Maybe we have some small errors.

67
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:33,350
Now we'll try to look at them.

68
00:09:33,350 --> 00:09:38,910
Say, I reset the frequency to MHz and 100 kHz.

69
00:09:41,390 --> 00:09:43,150
No distribution at all.

70
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:48,250
That is, it's a clear moment that the math doesn't work for us.

71
00:09:48,370 --> 00:09:50,110
How did we calculate the half wave?

72
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:56,510
We place at the base of the middle of the Tesla transformer our indicator.

73
00:09:57,470 --> 00:09:59,430
Approximately in the center of the winding.

74
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,810
And start adding frequency.

75
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:06,270
Lead smoothly by 10 kHz.

76
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:12,670
And see the moment when the lamp brightly lights up.

77
00:10:14,710 --> 00:10:25,410
The moment of maximum lamp glow corresponds for us to the frequency for the Tesla transformer equal to half wave.

78
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:33,150
Now examine by indicator that at the hot end the neon lamp doesn't glow.

79
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:35,590
Glow is present in the center.

80
00:10:36,390 --> 00:10:40,290
And also it doesn't glow at the base of the Tesla transformer.

81
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:45,590
And now what we got in fact.

82
00:10:45,990 --> 00:10:46,970
What frequency?

83
00:10:48,870 --> 00:10:53,130
Switch attention to the lab signal generator.

84
00:10:54,590 --> 00:11:02,250
And see, the half-wave resonance frequency corresponds to 1480 kHz.

85
00:11:03,350 --> 00:11:08,310
That is, we can make a conclusion — wow, what a difference.

86
00:11:08,890 --> 00:11:11,670
We clearly understand that the math here doesn't work.

87
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:21,910
Now I'll also do a measurement of the spectral range of this Tesla transformer with the help of a spectrum analyzer.

88
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:29,850
Maybe I did something incorrectly somewhere, and the spectrum analyzer will show us the whole spectral range 100%.

89
00:11:30,070 --> 00:11:32,690
Let's move to the experiment with the spectrum analyzer.

90
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:45,330
The optimal variant for tracking the resonance transformer frequency is the method of receiving it onto an antenna without connecting probes to this system.

91
00:11:45,990 --> 00:11:52,170
Pay attention that the lab signal generator is now disconnected from the one turn.

92
00:11:52,970 --> 00:11:56,230
And it's generally off to not create interference.

93
00:11:56,230 --> 00:12:03,610
Now we check in this experiment the accuracy of tuning our Tesla transformer to quarter wave.

94
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:13,790
You can pay attention that a spectral peak appears periodically on the device.

95
00:12:14,390 --> 00:12:17,510
This is the spike that jumps.

96
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:19,190
It's very well visible.

97
00:12:19,710 --> 00:12:23,050
I installed a marker on it.

98
00:12:23,170 --> 00:12:29,650
The marker frequency that shows by maximum is 500.1 kHz.

99
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:34,570
What does the appearance of this spike testify to?

100
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:48,670
That this Tesla transformer, when affected by some external radio waves from distant radio station transmitters or — as you could see, one spike slipped through.

101
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:51,170
Say, there's thunderstorm activity going somewhere.

102
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:54,370
Receiving it, it reacts.

103
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:57,730
And so I apply our frequency 500 kHz.

104
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:04,750
See, the spectral peak immediately grew multiple times.

105
00:13:05,730 --> 00:13:12,970
And the presence of my hand, when I approach, the amplitude decreases.

106
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:15,050
This testifies to accurate tuning.

107
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:23,030
Also at this frequency the next spectral peaks of the range of our transformer start being tracked.

108
00:13:23,710 --> 00:13:30,050
Now I'll change the frequency and we'll observe the spectrogram further.

109
00:13:30,990 --> 00:13:32,830
I start increasing the frequency.

110
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:37,210
The step will be 10 kHz.

111
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,460
We see detuning.

112
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,800
Amplitude falls.

113
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:50,960
And the peak moves.

114
00:13:52,060 --> 00:13:56,480
Here now is our math-calculated frequency 1 MHz.

115
00:13:56,660 --> 00:13:59,760
See how small it is on this transformer.

116
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,340
I raise further.

117
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:03,640
Observe the growth.

118
00:14:05,460 --> 00:14:08,700
And look where the maximum will be on such a frequency.

119
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:15,350
Our maximum

120
00:14:20,170 --> 00:14:25,730
corresponds to 1.5 MHz.

121
00:14:25,930 --> 00:14:32,450
Our measurements with neon lamp help were practically accurate.

122
00:14:32,450 --> 00:14:37,790
In the course of these measurements the frequency was calculated at 1480 kHz.

123
00:14:38,610 --> 00:14:43,590
Now I'll move the marker and look at the frequency.

124
00:14:48,830 --> 00:14:50,170
Here's the frequency.

125
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:54,050
See that the marker moved up.

126
00:14:54,130 --> 00:14:59,130
And here it corresponds to 1500 kHz.

127
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:12,810
At that, if we return to our Tesla transformer, at this frequency, as we remember, the neon lamp glows in the center.

128
00:15:14,670 --> 00:15:35,750
Now I'll slightly raise the voltage so it lit, because for half-wave distribution I literally added 4 V, and this was already enough so the neon bulb lit.

129
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:49,170
Because the quarter-wave signal by voltage antinode is higher than at half-wave distribution.

130
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:59,000
What interesting can we notice on the spectrum analyzer?

131
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:07,700
We see that next frequencies are tracked for us.

132
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:10,340
Here they are, the spectral peaks that appear.

133
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:16,980
And this peak that jumps for us — this is our frequency 500 kHz.

134
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:32,100
That is, we see the range of frequencies of our Tesla transformer — that when we put it at half wave, both 500 kHz and subsequent frequencies were also excited.

135
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:38,560
Now I'll sweep through frequency, and we'll write out its frequency characteristic.

136
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:41,620
Move further.

137
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:47,060
So, the step will lead also by 10 kHz.

138
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:54,290
Go to the next maximum.

139
00:16:55,330 --> 00:16:59,410
Remember by cells where the next peak was.

140
00:17:00,370 --> 00:17:03,450
And at the next peak we'll have amplitude growth.

141
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:05,490
Here the amplitude started growing.

142
00:17:06,870 --> 00:17:08,330
Here is its maximum.

143
00:17:10,790 --> 00:17:19,410
The frequency by lab signal generator is 2990 kHz for us.

144
00:17:22,650 --> 00:17:24,850
Look at the frequency.

145
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:31,740
The peak moved.

146
00:17:33,420 --> 00:17:37,740
And see the frequency 2990 kHz.

147
00:17:38,060 --> 00:17:39,820
Go further by frequency.

148
00:17:48,580 --> 00:17:52,100
And here see the growth of the peak.

149
00:17:52,580 --> 00:17:54,000
The next frequency

150
00:17:59,020 --> 00:18:04,640
3840 kHz.

151
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:13,510
Look does it correspond.

152
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,480
All corresponds.

153
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:19,940
3840.

154
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:26,480
Now we fully know the frequency range of this Tesla transformer.

155
00:18:26,780 --> 00:18:28,960
In those frequencies we can work out.

156
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:38,940
The whole scale now from 100 kHz start to the 5 MHz band in which we capture the spectral range.

157
00:18:38,940 --> 00:18:50,400
All experiments that I conducted with the spectrum analyzer can be conducted with an oscilloscope and lab signal generator present.

158
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:52,940
Only now the course of the experiment will be different.

159
00:18:53,840 --> 00:19:01,400
The same antenna that's now on the spectrum analyzer, we move to the oscilloscope.

160
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:06,240
Or hang nearby with the Tesla transformer its probe in the air.

161
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:13,580
And further change the frequency on the one turn with the help of the lab signal generator.

162
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:25,640
And write down for yourself all maxima and amplitudes the oscilloscope will fix at changing frequency on the lab signal generator.

163
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:28,620
The frequency picture will be the same.

164
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:34,980
Simply with the spectrum analyzer present this is conducted much more effectively and faster.

165
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:36,840
That's the whole difference.

166
00:19:37,660 --> 00:19:42,120
Now by fact we can observe frequency distributions.

167
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:47,200
Quarter, half wave, three quarters, and four quarters is a wave.

168
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:52,340
Those frequencies we can still really work at with electronics help.

169
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:56,960
You see they don't obey math.

170
00:19:58,160 --> 00:20:04,840
Say, if we'd found through math the wavelength, we'd have 500 kHz multiplied by 4.

171
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,900
It should correspond to 2 MHz.

172
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,260
And you see what frequency we have by fact.

173
00:20:10,420 --> 00:20:14,360
So I don't recommend applying math.

174
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:21,160
In this case this question — how the person did the calculation — we cross out.

175
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:24,800
Now the essence of the physical phenomenon.

176
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:31,120
Why such an interesting moment happens with frequency distribution.

177
00:20:32,780 --> 00:20:39,760
The thing is, these moments very brightly manifest themselves in resonance systems.

178
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:49,300
In classical systems where wave distribution goes, they don't behave like this, as namely in wave resonators.

179
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:52,620
Shortening coefficients are also applied there.

180
00:20:52,620 --> 00:20:57,620
But in our case this manifests itself very brightly.

181
00:20:58,620 --> 00:21:03,320
Let's examine the first case when the system stands at quarter.

182
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:06,360
The common system with grounding at half wave.

183
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:14,080
Here the spiral-wave resonator effectively affects 2 times less than in the system at half wave.

184
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:20,980
That is, in this case in the coil spiral half a wave fits, and here only quarter.

185
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:23,100
So the influence in this case increases.

186
00:21:24,420 --> 00:21:35,060
And the interesting effect is observed that the wave speed in the spiral wave resonator grows compared to wave speed that moves simply in a straight conductor.

187
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:38,280
Paradoxical as it is, here's the interest.

188
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:49,980
Also it should be mentioned that the wave distributes not only in the wire to the grounding, but also in the soil to which this grounding is connected.

189
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:59,760
That is, from the cold end to the wire end, effectively the wave walks not only in this part, but also in the soils.

190
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:01,340
All depends on the soils.

191
00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:11,240
And we have the moment that we now know that as frequency rises, physical wavelength meters decrease.

192
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:23,900
And so to in our case at half wave we fit our spiral wave resonator wire length precisely half wave, we also should raise frequency.

193
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:25,800
Exactly then it'll fit.

194
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:29,880
Reduce physical meters and put it into coil length.

195
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:36,620
Now a reasonable question arises or will arise from viewers.

196
00:22:36,620 --> 00:22:42,540
Why these dances with a tambourine and switching the coil to half wave?

197
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:49,500
The thing is, for the build of a working system the presence of a half-wave vibrator is mandatory.

198
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:55,060
Without it any serious energy you won't get.

199
00:22:55,180 --> 00:23:03,360
So no one is going anywhere from tuning the receiving coil to half wave.

200
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:08,320
And once more pay attention to the build of this coil.

201
00:23:09,340 --> 00:23:17,720
I made it with thick copper wire, to remove active resistance specifically from it.

202
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:21,980
Further I'll make my own generator.

203
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:28,080
On this, all successful experiments and best wishes.

204
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:38,700
In the next video, which I'll try to film faster, another interesting question was asked.

205
00:23:39,340 --> 00:23:45,180
How does one Tesla transformer affect another with the help of its fields?

206
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,660
What distributions happen?

